        Catch attention with custom sail flags that move with the breeze.

        • 4 size options
        • Durable polyester material
        • Standard or premium material options
        • Single- & double-sided printing
        • Wind-resistant up to 37 mph
        • Pole, ground stake & carrying case included (may ship separately)
        • Additional bases available for purchase

        Note: For important information on how to assemble your flag, download this PDF guide.

        Stand out from afar

        Looking to create eye-catching advertising displays for your business? Our custom sail flags are designed to make your logo and graphics stand tall and visible. With a distinctive curved shape and impressive height – up to 15' 7" – these attention-grabbing flags deliver your message in a polished, approachable way. Perfect for tradeshows, events, beaches or right outside your storefront, sail flag signs are a go-to for small businesses in automotive, real estate, fitness, food and religious organizations. As they sway gently in the breeze, sail banners to draw people in without overwhelming your space.

        Easy setup anywhere

        Our sail flags are designed for quick setup: Your set includes a durable, weather-resistant polyester flag, sturdy pole, ground stake and soft carrying case for portable transport. We have 4 flag base options – whether you’re promoting outdoors, in a lobby or showroom or at a community event. With standard or premium material options, single- or double-sided printing and wind resistance up to 37 mph, your promotional signage will stand strong in a variety of settings.

        Customize in minutes

        Designing your custom sail flag is quick and simple. Start with one of our professionally-designed templates or upload your own graphics and logo. Add images, text or even a QR code to create a display that’s uniquely yours. Our online design tools make customization easy, and our expert printing ensures a high-quality, vibrant result. Once you’re done ordering, we’ll deliver everything to your door, ready to display.

        VistaPrint offers Sail Flags design templates in assorted styles.

        Frequently asked questions

        We recommend following these steps for a smooth (and stress-free) setup:

        1. Assemble pole: Attach the pieces of your flagpole, and then add the antenna to the top of the pole.

        2. Add flag: Feed the antenna through the pocket that runs along the side of your printed flag (the hole is quite small, but it’s there).

        3. Attach base: Place the prong on the top of your base into the hole at the bottom of the flagpole.

        4. Secure flag: Make sure the bungee is attached to both the custom flag and the hook on the flagpole.

        Yes, you can choose between single or double-sided printing on our advertising flags. Single-sided flags are more translucent, which lets the flag design (and sunlight) shine through, while our more opaque, double-sided flags offer richer color saturation. Unfortunately, we do not offer double-sided printing on our air mesh flags.

        The flagpole is black, and is .5” wide. We offer fiberglass and aluminum poles, with a bungee to connect them. It also has a plastic hook that is used to secure the custom flag to the pole – and you can adjust the hook to increase or decrease the flag tension.

        Custom sail flags are printed using dye sublimation on translucent polyester. The resulting banners are slightly sheer, which lets the design show through to be visible on both sides. If you choose double-sided printing for your flags, your flag will include 2 layers of printed material and a third opaque layer in between for a more saturated look.

        Our flags are crafted using dye sublimation on translucent polyester. This process creates slightly sheer banners, allowing the design to be visible on both sides. For a more opaque appearance, you can opt for double-sided printing, which incorporates two layers of material. Rest assured, our advanced printing technology ensures all flags are fire-certified for safety.

        Absolutely. Sail flags can be safely washed in a washing machine. We recommend using cold water and allowing the flag to air dry. With proper care, your flag can last up to a year.

        Here are the weights for our flag base options:

        Ground Stake: 2.9 lbs

        Drive-Over Base: 5.6 lbs

        Auger Base: 2.2 lbs

        Pavement Base: 24 lbs when filled with water

        For more information on all our base options, click here.

        Dimensions vary depending on the size of the branded flag, as well as the amount of tension applied when setting up. Please see the tables below:

        Size including pole Height Width Flag (height only)
        7.5’ 7’1” 1.78’ 5’8”
        10’ 9’10” 2.21’ 6’10”
        13’ 12'8.5" 2.53’ 9’6’
        15’ 15’7’ 2.98’ 12’3”
        The premium material features a matte finish on one side and a semi-gloss finish on the other, and has a completely crease-free surface. With a weight of 120 g/m², its softness gives it a more premium feel and appearance compared to our standard flag material, which weighs in at a lighter 110 g/m².

        All flag orders are packaged neatly and shipped in sturdy boxes. If you ordered a complete flag kit (with the flag fabric, pole, choice of base and carrying case), you may receive your order in multiple boxes, shipped separately.
